# Summary by age group
time.summary.by.group <- marathon_data %>%
  group_by(agegroup) %>%
  summarise(
    Count = n(),
    Min = min(time),
    Max = max(time),
    Mean = mean(time),
    Median = median(time),
    SD = sd(time)
  )

time.summary.by.group

marathon_data %>%
  # Grouped by age
  group_by(agegroup) %>%
  # Create plots for each group
  group_walk(~ {
    measures <- summarise(.x, Mean = mean(time), Median = median(time))
    
    plot.for.age.group <- ggplot(.x, aes(time)) +
      geom_histogram(alpha = 0.8,color= "#0073C2FF", binwidth = 600, fill = "light blue", show.legend = FALSE) +
      geom_vline(aes(xintercept = Mean), measures, color = "red") + 
      geom_vline(aes(xintercept = Median), measures, color = "green") +
      labs(
        title = paste("Histogram for age group:", .y$agegroup),
        x = "Time in seconds",
        y = "Number of individuals"
      ) +
      scale_x_continuous(breaks = log_breaks(10), labels = label_number(scale_cut = cut_short_scale()))
    
    print(plot.for.age.group)
    ggsave(filename = paste0("age_group - ", .y$agegroup, ".png"), plot = plot.for.age.group)
  })

#Task2

#Null Hypothesis (H₀): All age groups have the same mean finish time
#Alternative Hypothesis (H₁): At least one age group has a different mean finish time

# Perform ANOVA to test if finish times differ between age groups
anova_result <- aov(time ~ agegroup, data = marathon_data)

# Tidy the ANOVA result into a table
anova_table <- tidy(anova_result)
# Display the table in RStudio Viewer
kable(anova_table, caption = "ANOVA Results Table")
ANOVA Results Table

Residuals 2823 12523467776 4436227 NA NA 
# Create the table using the `gridExtra` package
anova_table_plot <- tableGrob(anova_table)

# Save the table as a .png file
ggsave("anova_table.png", anova_table_plot, width = 6, height = 5, units = "in")

#age group significantly affects marathon finish times
#We reject Null Hypothesis (H₀)

#Task3

#Null Hypothesis (H₀) : The mean finish times for two specific age groups are equal. 
#Alternative Hypothesis (H₁): The mean finish times for two specific age groups are not equal.

# ---Two-sample t-tests---
t_test<- pairwise.t.test(marathon_data$time, marathon_data$agegroup, pool.sd = TRUE, p.adjust.method = "none")
t_test

# Bonferroni correction
Bonferroni_results <- pairwise.t.test(marathon_data$time, marathon_data$agegroup, p.adjust.method = "bonferroni")

#Task4

# Extract p-values for all pairwise comparisons from t-tests
t_test_data <- as.data.frame(as.table(t_test$p.value)) %>%
  rename(Comparison = Var1, Group2 = Var2, P_value_before_adjustment = Freq) %>%
  mutate(Comparison = paste(Comparison, Group2, sep = "-")) %>%
  select(Comparison, P_value_before_adjustment) %>%
  filter(complete.cases(.))

# Extract Bonferroni-adjusted p-values
bonferroni_data <- as.data.frame(as.table(Bonferroni_results$p.value)) %>%
  rename(Comparison = Var1, Group2 = Var2, P_value_after_Bonferroni_adjustment = Freq) %>%
  mutate(Comparison = paste(Comparison, Group2, sep = "-")) %>%
  select(Comparison, P_value_after_Bonferroni_adjustment) %>%
  filter(complete.cases(.))

# Extract pairwise comparisons from Tukey HSD results
tukey_data <- as.data.frame(Tukey_results$agegroup) %>%
  rownames_to_column(var = "Comparison") %>%
  mutate(P_value_after_Tukey_HSD = round(`p adj`, 8)) %>%
  select(Comparison, P_value_after_Tukey_HSD)

# Combine all results into a single table
combined_results <- t_test_data %>%
  left_join(bonferroni_data, by = "Comparison") %>%
  left_join(tukey_data, by = "Comparison") %>%
  select(Comparison, P_value_before_adjustment, P_value_after_Bonferroni_adjustment, P_value_after_Tukey_HSD)
  
# View the final table
print(combined_results)
